# Pin the working tree to LF on every platform.
#
# Git on Windows checks out CRLF by default. The generators behind
# tests/docs.rs emit LF, so without this a Windows checkout compares CRLF
# files against LF renderings and fails all three doc guards with a
# thoroughly misleading "no longer matches the clap definitions" — the docs
# are fine; the checkout isn't. Blessing there would rewrite every line of
# all three files.
#
# `text=auto` still lets git detect and leave binary files alone.
* text=auto eol=lf
